title: Why can't I open some photos or videos on my phone?
answer:
The phone does not support the file format. 

 The phone memory is insufficient. 

 The file is damaged. 

 The file is copyright-protected (for example, a .dcf file). 

 The phone does not have sufficient resources. Close some running third-party applications and try again. 

 [An unknown error occurred in the camera or the phone's OS. Restart the phone and try again.]()
